## Environment & Dependencies

This project was developed within the **Stanford RNA 3D Folding Challenge (Kaggle)** environment.  
The competition enforces strict **offline execution rules**, meaning Kaggle notebooks **cannot use internet access** during training or inference to prevent external data leakage.

Because of this restriction, all required resources must be available locally inside the runtime environment.

To ensure the project runs fully offline and remains reproducible, the implementation relies on **Biopython** for handling biological sequence data and parsing RNA sequence information without requiring external downloads.

All required dependencies are listed below:
